Meet Ruby, a jolly and vivacious 64 lbs, female who loves spending time with volunteers. Just over 1 year old, she’s still puppy-like and would thrive with an active family who will play with her, teach her and make her a part of the family. This bubbly, lovable sweetheart came to the shelter on Jan 11, 2017 as an OWNER SURRENDER for landlord issues. Her previous owners reported they had Ruby her whole life and she is friendly with children and company. They kept her inside so she is housebroken and the hard kennel floors are extra rough -- she’s used to life in a home. Can you open up your home to this sweet-faced girl and show her the love of a forever family? Please come and meet her! ❣️

🐾🇫🇷Adoption Update:

Dudley has been in Europe for a month now, has an EU passport (lucky!) and has just completed a road trip up to the Netherlands from the South of France and back again. He seems to be quite a good traveller, which is just as well- in the past month he's been in a plane, cars, busses, trains - I've yet to try him in the basket of my bike! He was welcome in the Dutch hotel room, and in the restaurants. So welcome everywhere that the biggest worry was his reaction to all the outpouring of affection he was getting! He is still very defensive, and people were all over him, which could be nerve-racking. Luckily, when this scruffy little dog tried to be tough, they all just laughed. It makes a difference being in the midst of a population that generally hasn't been trained from a young age to fear all other species.
Anyway, I think it's fair to say he has landed on all four paws, with all this fresh air and freedom, but he is also a great walking companion, transforms the house and, it turns out, is quite the social asset!
.

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Greta a one your old petite English Coonhound mix. She was recently rescued from an area shelter after being found emaciated and alone. She is currently in her foster home and adjusting well. She is great with all people and dogs. She is very treat motivated and is doing well on leash walks. She loves be outside and explore her surroundings. She has a fun bounce to her gait on walks and will bring smiles to everyone she meets. She is crate and house trained. She would do well in a home with someone that has fenced in yard or that is able to take her for long walks. She currently weighs around 30lbs and after putting on some much needed weight will weigh around 40lbs. She is current on vaccines, microchipped and will be spayed on January 4th 2018. We are currently accepting applications on Greta. She is ready and waiting to meet her forever family. He was recently rescued from a local shelter. Frank is currently in a foster home and adjusting well. He adores children of all ages and is a very social boy. AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!! Meet Fiona a beautiful 8 month old petite hound/boxer mix born around June 2017. Fiona is an affectionate girl that loves to give kisses to everyone she meets. She was recently rescued from an area shelter and is adjusting well in her foster home. This sweet girl has great house manners, is crate and house trained. She walks well on leash and would love to be someone’s walking or running buddy. Fiona would do well in an apartment setting or in a house. She would be ok in a home where someone works during the week. She would benefit from daily walks, if left for longer time periods. Fiona is very treat motivated and already knows sit. She is learning what great fun car rides can be. She would love a family to call her own where she can get all the love and attention she deserves. She currently weights around 30lbs and will weigh around 40lbs full grown. She is current on vaccines, spayed and microchipped. Born in September, 2017, Bruno and his Mom and two brothers (Mars and Cat Stevens) were rescued from a trash drop behind a strip center. The residents of this area abuse small animals and the hawks circle looking for food. Bruno was the smallest brother and initially the quietest. But now that he is in his foster home, Bruno is energized and always wanting to play. He has had an injury to his eye but the vet is trying to save it and believes he has some vision in it. Bruno has been fully vetted. Contact HOPE at www.homelesspets.net to meet Bruno
